Residents in the area raised an alarm after they sighted smoke from the premises of the company at 6:55 am. According to Channels Television, following the distress calls, the Kano State Fire Service arrived at the scene at about 7:00 am to contain the fire. While the exact cause of the incident is yet to be known, the public relations officer of the service, Yusuf Abdullahi, said it may have been caused by hoodlums smoking at a nearby refuse dump.